cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of searching for predictive models, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed iterative procedure involves deriving sets of non-linear features, which is also a common technique in machine learning and data science (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of non-linear features in computer vision (cs.CV) and the likelihood of the models increasing with each iteration, which is a concept commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
